# Project Core Rules

## Work style
- Always read `Agent.md` before starting any implementation task.
- Understand existing code before editing; keep changes focused and minimal.
- Do not modify unrelated files or large formatting-only areas.
- Prefer small, testable steps and report what changed clearly.

## Code quality
- Prefer ES6+ syntax and modern JavaScript patterns by default.
- Keep functions cohesive and avoid duplicate logic.
- Use clear names and early returns over deep nesting.
- Add comments only when logic is non-obvious.

## Safety
- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, or credentials.
- Avoid destructive git operations unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve backward compatibility unless the task requires breaking changes.

## Validation
- Run the most relevant checks/tests after edits when possible.
- If checks cannot be run, state what was not verified and why.

## Communication
- Prefer Vietnamese when explaining code and implementation decisions.
- Explain trade-offs briefly when multiple implementation choices exist.
- Ask for confirmation before high-impact changes (schema, API contracts, auth flow).
